   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>THE TRAINING AND THE PRACTICE OF THE VITAL GROUPS MESSAGE TWO THE THREE ENEMIES TODAY Scripture Reading: Rev 3:1-2; Rom 12:1-10; Rev 3:14-18, 20; Rom 12:11; John 15:2a; Matt 25:24-30 OUTLINE The deadness of Sardis Rev 3:1-2: To be conquered in the Body life Rom 12:3-10.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>By: Presenting our bodies a living sacrifice to God Rom 12:1.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Being transformed from the fashion of this age by the renewing of our mind Rom 12:2.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The lukewarmness of Laodicea Rev 3:14-16: To be conquered by the seeking of the riches of Christ Rev 3:17-18, 20.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>By: Not being slothful in zeal Rom 12:11a.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Being burning in spirit, serving the Lord Rom 12:11b.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The barrenness of the degenerating believers: To be conquered in desperation.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>By: Fearing to be cut off from the enjoyment of Christ's supply in this age John 15:2a.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Caring for the discipline in the coming age Matt 25:24-30.</S>
   </TEXT>
